tps0=t.clock()

# Removing links with "www." (example : tweet n° 2534)
for i in range(0,len(tweet1.text)):
    
    c=[]
    
    for k in range(0,len(tweet1.text[i])):
        if tweet1.text[i][k][0:3] == 'www' :
            c.append(k)
        if tweet1.text[i][k][0:4] == 'http' :
            c.append(k)
        if tweet1.text[i][k][0:10] == 'youtubecom' :
            c.append(k)
            
    if c!=[] :
        tweet1.text[i]=np.delete(tweet1.text[i], c).tolist()
        
tps1=t.clock()
print("Temps execution en mn :",(tps1 - tps0)/60)

In [43]:
def replaceTwoOrMore(s):
    #look for 2 or more repetitions of character and replace with the character itself
    pattern = re.compile(r"(.)\1{1,}", re.DOTALL)
    return pattern.sub(r"\1\1", s)

                  ':-)', 'like', 'love','triumph', 'triumphal', 'triumphant', 'victory']

In [79]:
def proba(i):
    p= float (len(df[df.iloc[:,i]==1]) / len(df.index))
    return p
In [80]:
def coproba(i,j):
    p= float (len(df[ (df.iloc[:,i]==1) & (df.iloc[:,j]==1 )]) / len(df.index))
    return p
In [81]:
import math
def pmi(i,term): 
    if term in df.columns:  
        j= df.columns.get_loc(term)
        denom= proba(i) * proba(j)
        if coproba(i,j)!=0: p= math.log(coproba(i,j) / denom)
        else: p=0
    else: p=0
    return p
In [85]:
def semantic_orientation(i):
    positive_assoc = sum(pmi(i,tx) for tx in positive_vocab)
    #print positive_assoc
    negative_assoc = sum(pmi(i,tx) for tx in negative_vocab)
    #print negative_assoc
    so = positive_assoc - negative_assoc   
    return so

def test_classifier(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, classifier):
    print("")
    print("==========================================================================================================\
          ==========")
    classifier_name = str(type(classifier).__name__)
    print("Testing " + classifier_name)
    now = time()
    list_of_labels = sorted(list(set(y_train)))
    model = classifier.fit(X_train, y_train)
    print("Learing time {0}s".format(time() - now))
    now = time()
    predictions = model.predict(X_test)
    print("Predicting time {0}s".format(time() - now))

    precision = precision_score(y_test, predictions, average=None, pos_label=None, labels=list_of_labels)
    recall = recall_score(y_test, predictions, average=None, pos_label=None, labels=list_of_labels)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, predictions)
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, predictions, average=None, pos_label=None, labels=list_of_labels)
    print("================================================= Results ===============================================\
          ===========")
    print("         policy    attack    support    information    mobilization    personal    constituency    media\
            other")
    print("F1       " + str(f1))
    print("Precision" + str(precision))
    print("Recall   " + str(recall))
    print("Accuracy " + str(accuracy))
    print("=========================================================================================================\
          ===========")
    
    
    return precision, recall, accuracy, f1

def test_classifiers_whole(data, target):
    tps0=t.clock()

    # Classifiers
    logi = linear_model.LogisticRegression()
    bn = BernoulliNB()
    svm_  = LinearSVC()
    rf   = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=1)
    boost = xgb.XGBClassifier(objective='multi:softmax')   #Specify that it's a multiclass classification
    nnet = MLPClassifier()
    vot = VotingClassifier(estimators=[('bn', bn), ('boost', boost)] , voting='hard')

    # Number of iterations
    B=3 # to test the loop : use B=3 instead

    # Parameters grids
    listMethGrid=[logi, bn, svm_ ,rf,boost, nnet,vot]
    arrayErreur=np.empty((B,8))
    
    for i in range(B):
        print i
        X_train,X_test,Y_train,Y_test=train_test_split(data, target,test_size=0.2)
        scaler = StandardScaler()  
        scaler.fit(X_train)  

        X_train = scaler.transform(X_train)  
        X_test = scaler.transform(X_test)

        # Computation of test error
        for j,method in enumerate(listMethGrid):
            methFit=method.fit(X_train, Y_train)
            arrayErreur[i,j]=methFit.score(X_test,Y_test)
    
    tps1=t.clock()
    exec_time= (tps1 - tps0)/60
    print("Temps execution en mn :",exec_time)
    
    
    dataframeErreur=pd.DataFrame(arrayErreur,columns=["Logit","BN","SVM","RF","XGBoost", "NNET","VOT","..."])       
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15,7))
    dataframeErreur[["Logit","BN","SVM","RF","XGBoost", "NNET","VOT"]].boxplot(return_type='dict')
    ax.set_xticklabels(["Logit","BN","SVM","RF","XGBoost", "NNET","VOT"],fontsize=30)
    plt.show()
    
    return exec_time, arrayErreur

def test_classifiers_categories(data, target, category):
    
    # Set 1 to the specified category 0 otherwise
    target_cat = target.copy()
    idx_1=target_cat.loc[target_cat==category].index
    idx_0=target_cat.loc[target_cat!=category].index
    target_cat.loc[idx_1]=1
    target_cat.loc[idx_0]=0
   
    tps0=t.clock()

    # Classifiers
    logi = linear_model.LogisticRegression()
    bn = BernoulliNB()
    svm_  = LinearSVC()
    rf   = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=1)
    boost = xgb.XGBClassifier()   #Specify that it's a multiclass classification
    nnet = MLPClassifier()
    vot = VotingClassifier(estimators=[('bn', bn), ('boost', boost)] , voting='hard')

    # Number of iterations
    B=3 # to test the loop 

    # Parameters grids
    listMethGrid=[logi,bn, svm_ ,rf,boost,nnet,vot ]
    arrayErreur=np.empty((B,8))
    
    for i in range(B):
        print i
        X_train,X_test,Y_train,Y_test=train_test_split(data,target_cat,test_size=0.2)
        scaler = StandardScaler()  
        scaler.fit(X_train)  

        X_train = scaler.transform(X_train)  
        X_test = scaler.transform(X_test)

        # Computation of test error
        for j,method in enumerate(listMethGrid):
            methFit=method.fit(X_train, Y_train)
            arrayErreur[i,j]=methFit.score(X_test,Y_test)
  
    tps1=t.clock()
    exec_time= (tps1 - tps0)/60
    print("Temps execution en mn :",exec_time)
    
    
    dataframeErreur=pd.DataFrame(arrayErreur,columns=["Logit","BN","SVM","RF","XGBoost", "NNET","VOT","..."])       
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15,7))
    dataframeErreur[["Logit","BN","SVM","RF","XGBoost", "NNET","VOT"]].boxplot(return_type='dict')
    ax.set_xticklabels(["Logit","BN","SVM","RF","XGBoost", "NNET","VOT"],fontsize=30)
    plt.show()
    
    return exec_time, arrayErreur

def test_classifier(X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, classifier):
    print("")
    print("==================================================================================")
    classifier_name = str(type(classifier).__name__)
    print("Testing " + classifier_name)
    now = time()
    list_of_labels = sorted(list(set(y_train)))
    model = classifier.fit(X_train, y_train)
    print("Learing time {0}s".format(time() - now))
    now = time()
    predictions = model.predict(X_test)
    print("Predicting time {0}s".format(time() - now))

    precision = precision_score(y_test, predictions)
    recall = recall_score(y_test, predictions)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, predictions)
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, predictions)
    print("=================================== Results ======================================")
    print("         bias")
    print("F1       " + str(f1))
    print("Precision" + str(precision))
    print("Recall   " + str(recall))
    print("Accuracy " + str(accuracy))
    print("===================================================================================")

    return model

    methFit=method.fit(X_train, Y_train)
    preds=methFit.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]

    fpr, tpr, _ = metrics.roc_curve(Y_test, preds)
    df = pd.DataFrame(dict(fpr=fpr, tpr=tpr))

    plt.plot(df['fpr'],df['tpr'],label=labels[i])

    auc_score=metrics.roc_auc_score(Y_test, preds)
